<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06053c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06053c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06053c"> 53(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> repress pain</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Groos &hellip; signale comme propres &agrave; fortifier ce pouvoir d&apos;inhibition un certain nombre de jeux qui constituent de vrais exercices de r&eacute;pression des mouvements r&eacute;flexes, instinctifs ou habituels. Tels sont les jeux o&ugrave; l&apos;enfant s&apos;efforce d&apos;emp&ecirc;cher les paupi&egrave;res de se clore devant la menace d&apos;un coup sur l&apos;oil;- les jeux de r&eacute;pression du rire; - <mark>de r&eacute;pression de la douleur</mark>: t&acirc;cher, par exemple, d&apos;&ecirc;tre impassible lors des pertes subies aux jeux de hasard; [Groos ... points out as being able to fortify this power of inhibition a certain number of games which constitute real exercises of repression of reflex movements, instinctive or habitual. Such are the games in which the child endeavors to prevent the eyelids from closing at the threat of a blow on the eye: games of repression of laughter; - repression of pain: try, for example, to be impassive during losses suffered by games of chance; <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 110 footnote</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
